{"lc": 1, "type": "constructor", "id": ["langchain", "schema", "document", "Document"], "kwargs": {"metadata": {"doc_id": "b3418120-5527-4a63-9378-16daa57c8208", "source": "NexaCorp Policy Handbook v5.2", "part": "5. IT, Data & Security Policies", "section": "5.2 Information Classification & Handling", "subsection": "5.2.2 Data Retention & Disposal", "raw_content": "All data created, collected, or processed in the course of NexaCorp business is subject to the NexaCorp Data Retention Schedule (DRS), maintained by the Data Governance Council. Employees must not delete or destroy data that may be subject to a litigation hold (Legal Hold Notice issued by the CLO's office) or regulatory investigation, regardless of the DRS schedule. When data reaches the end of its retention period, it must be disposed of using approved methods: Electronic Data: Cryptographic erasure or verified overwrite using NIST 800-88-compliant tools. Deletion from trash/recycle bin alone is insufficient. Hardware Containing Data: IT Asset Management team must be notified for all equipment disposals. Unauthorised disposal of NexaCorp hardware is prohibited.", "type": "text", "text": "Part: 5. IT, Data & Security Policies\n            Section: 5.2 Information Classification & Handling\n            Subsection: 5.2.2 Data Retention & Disposal\n            All data created, collected, or processed in the course of NexaCorp business is subject to the NexaCorp Data Retention Schedule (DRS), maintained by the Data Governance Council. Employees must not delete or destroy data that may be subject to a litigation hold (Legal Hold Notice issued by the CLO's office) or regulatory investigation, regardless of the DRS schedule. When data reaches the end of its retention period, it must be disposed of using approved methods: Electronic Data: Cryptographic erasure or verified overwrite using NIST 800-88-compliant tools. Deletion from trash/recycle bin alone is insufficient. Hardware Containing Data: IT Asset Management team must be notified for all equipment disposals. Unauthorised disposal of NexaCorp hardware is prohibited."}, "page_content": "Part: 5. IT, Data & Security Policies\n            Section: 5.2 Information Classification & Handling\n            Subsection: 5.2.2 Data Retention & Disposal\n            All data created, collected, or processed in the course of NexaCorp business is subject to the NexaCorp Data Retention Schedule (DRS), maintained by the Data Governance Council. Employees must not delete or destroy data that may be subject to a litigation hold (Legal Hold Notice issued by the CLO's office) or regulatory investigation, regardless of the DRS schedule. When data reaches the end of its retention period, it must be disposed of using approved methods: Electronic Data: Cryptographic erasure or verified overwrite using NIST 800-88-compliant tools. Deletion from trash/recycle bin alone is insufficient. Hardware Containing Data: IT Asset Management team must be notified for all equipment disposals. Unauthorised disposal of NexaCorp hardware is prohibited.", "type": "Document"}}